The paper deals with the problem of license plate re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep convolutional nets and neural networks, which are common techniques in machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of the Fisher vector, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval and computer vision, making cs.CR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the generalizability of the proposed approach to datasets dissimilar to the training corpus, which is a topic commonly discussed in multimedia computing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
